vm-bhyve is a popular management system for FreeBSD bhyve virtual machines.
It provides a CLI tool called 'vm', which acts as a front-end for bhyve.

Some of the main features include:

 - Windows/UEFI support
 - Simple commands to create/start/stop bhyve instances
 - Simple configuration file format
 - Virtual switches supporting vlans & nat (no manual tap or bridge devices
   needed)
 - ZFS support
 - FreeBSD/NetBSD/OpenBSD/Linux guest support
 - Automatic assignment of console devices to access guest console
 - Integration with rc.d startup/shutdown
 - Guest reboot handling
 - Designed with multiple compute nodes + shared storage in mind
   (NFS/iSCSI/etc)
 - Multiple datastores (1.1 only)
 - VNC graphics & tmux support (1.1 only. See wiki for instructions)

More details on the project's wiki: https://github.com/churchers/vm-bhyve/wiki

WWW: https://github.com/churchers/vm-bhyve
